        "subtopic": "Top 10 Important Historical Monuments",
        "content": "• Red Fort → Delhi, built by Shah Jahan (1638–1648), UNESCO site since 2007.\n\n• Taj Mahal → Agra, built by Shah Jahan (1631–1648), UNESCO site since 1983, one of the Seven Wonders of the World.\n\n• Qutub Minar → Delhi, built by Qutb-ud-din Aibak & later rulers (1193–1368), 73m tall tower.\n\n• Ajanta & Ellora Caves → Aurangabad, Maharashtra, Buddhist/Hindu/Jain rock-cut caves, 2nd BCE – 11th CE, UNESCO World Heritage.\n\n• Konark Sun Temple → Odisha, built by Eastern Ganga Dynasty (13th century), chariot-shaped temple.\n\n• Khajuraho Temples → Madhya Pradesh, Chandela Dynasty (950–1050), world-famous sculptures.\n\n• Hampi → Karnataka, capital of Vijayanagar Empire (14th century), UNESCO World Heritage.\n\n• Fatehpur Sikri → Agra, built by Akbar (1571–1585), ‘City of Victory’.\n\n• Sanchi Stupa → Madhya Pradesh, built by Ashoka (3rd century BCE), Buddhist site.\n\n• Mahabalipuram → Tamil Nadu, Pallava Dynasty (7th century), UNESCO World Heritage site."
